    feat(conference)(conference-detail): boundary Conference growth + toConference Option projection

    Branch 3 sub-commit 3.2. Project the optional detail-page fields Branch 3.1
    added to the Conference document (registrationUrl / scheduleUrl / mapEmbedUrl as
    OptionFromOptionalKey, hotels as an empty-able id-keyed list) into the read
    boundary the routes/components consume (boundary-discipline):

    - The boundary Conference interface grows registrationUrl / scheduleUrl /
      mapEmbedUrl as string | undefined and hotels as a plain {name, note?}[] — so
      React never sees an Option<string>, and Branch 4's section-skip gates on
      undefined / [] (the section-presence discriminator).
    - toConference projects each document Option via Option.getOrUndefined (the
      convention for ALL new optional Conference fields, matching the existing
      registration Option.isSome gate), and maps each Hotel to this locale's strings
      via a new toHotel helper (dropping the list-identity id from the read shape;
      the optional note stays string | undefined).
    - content.server.test.ts: pins the projection against the defaults — 2024 (every
      field present, hotel notes per-locale en/fr), 2026 (only registrationUrl, the
      RegFox live channel; rest skippable), 2025 (cancelled year, all absent).

