 48	 *     route/component shape (per-locale strings, `[start, end]` millisecond
 49	 *     tuples, leading-`/` image URLs) so component code is UNCHANGED.
 50	 *   - `use-the-platform`: the read cache is Effect's built-in
 51	 *     `Effect.cachedInvalidateWithTTL` — it single-flights concurrent
 52	 *     first-reads (a fetch in flight parks the other fibers on a latch and they
 53	 *     all get the one result, so the bucket is not stampeded) and hands back an
 54	 *     `invalidate` effect the editor's publish calls (`bust`). Within the TTL it
 55	 *     returns the *same* decoded `SiteContent` reference. **Documented staleness
 56	 *     window:** the built-in `invalidate` is a bare sync that only expires the
 57	 *     entry (`expiresAt = 0`); it does not pre-empt an in-flight refresh nor
 58	 *     clear its `running` flag. So a publish that lands while a refresh is
 59	 *     already fetching the bucket is masked: that refresh's `onExit` completes
 60	 *     with the *pre-publish* document and re-arms the TTL from its own
 61	 *     completion instant. Measured from the publish instant the stale window is
 62	 *     therefore `(the refresh's remaining bucket-read duration) + one TTL` — not
 63	 *     ≤ one TTL. For a 30s-TTL, low-write CMS this worst case (a multi-second
 64	 *     bucket read in flight + 30s) still stays inside D3's "visible on the next
 65	 *     read after the window" contract, so we take the platform primitive over a
 66	 *     hand-rolled epoch guard (`subtract-before-you-add`).
 67	 *   - `make-impossible-states-unrepresentable`: a Conference whose pricing is
 68	 *     undecided carries `registration: undefined` (the `Option.none()` in the
 69	 *     document), never empty tuples.
 70	 *
 71	 * The boundary types below reproduce the shape the routes/components already
 72	 * consume verbatim (`title`, the misnamed-but-rendered `theme` accent colour,
 73	 * `hero.image.{desktop,mobile}`, `hero.alt`, `[start, end]` ms `dates`, optional
 74	 * ms `registration`, `speakers[].img`, …) so migrating the loaders is a
 75	 * one-line swap and the rendered HTML is byte-for-byte the same.
 76	 */
